	(text "MSPM0G3507 — 64-QFN (RGZ), 9×9mm, 0.5mm pitch\n\nKey pin assignments (all 3.3V logic):\n  PA8  → PWM_LASER  (TIMA0_CCP0, laser bridge Q2a gate)\n  PA22 → PWM_DUMMY  (TIMA0_CCP0_CMPL, dummy bridge Q2b gate)\n  PA12 → VREF       (DAC0_OUT, 0–2.5V, sets laser current)\n  PB21 ← TRIGGER    (active-low, internal pull-up enabled)\n  PA10 → UART_TX    (UART0 TX → Pi GPIO15/RXD or CH340N)\n  PA11 ← UART_RX    (UART0 RX ← Pi GPIO14/TXD or CH340N)\n  PA19 ← SWCLK      (SWD clock from Pi GPIO23 or J_SWD pin 2)\n  PA20 ↔ SWDIO      (SWD data, Pi GPIO24 or J_SWD pin 3)\n  NRST ← NRST       (reset from Pi GPIO25 or J_SWD pin 1)\n\nDAC reference: internal 2.5V reference\nFirmware: laser_driver.c / laser_pwm_control.c (see Firmware/laserDriverTest)\nOscillator: internal 32 MHz"
		(at 110 50 0)
		(effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left top))
		(uuid "00000003-text-0000-0000-000000000001")
	)

	(text "Decoupling strategy:\n  4× 100nF (0402) on VDD pins — place one per pin\n  1× 10µF  (0805) bulk on VDD\n  1× 100nF (0402) on VDDA\n  1× 1µF   (0402) on VDDA bulk\nRoute VSS to thermal pad (EP) with many vias.\nVDDA and VSSA should be filtered separately\nwith a ferrite bead if DAC noise matters."
		(at 110 100 0)
		(effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left top))
		(uuid "00000003-text-0000-0000-000000000002")
	)

